WEBVTT

00:00:32.136 --> 00:00:35.013
THE JUDGE RETURNS

00:00:41.228 --> 00:00:42.229
What?

00:00:43.021 --> 00:00:44.189
Why is it empty?

00:00:45.065 --> 00:00:47.234
Those damn bastards!

00:00:47.693 --> 00:00:48.986
How did they hide so fast?

00:00:49.069 --> 00:00:50.988
Hey, calm down.

00:00:51.071 --> 00:00:54.741
Why are we searching here?
They cleared out a long time ago!

00:00:54.825 --> 00:00:55.826
The investment scammers

00:00:56.368 --> 00:00:57.619
only rent this space

00:00:57.703 --> 00:00:59.955
for investment seminars and events.

00:01:00.038 --> 00:01:01.039
What?

00:01:07.171 --> 00:01:09.506
Hey, Seong-dae invested 2.9 billion won.

00:01:09.590 --> 00:01:10.841
It's three billion in total.

00:01:11.550 --> 00:01:13.719
He'll catch on soon enough.
Better wrap it up.

00:01:14.011 --> 00:01:15.554
I'm already on it.

00:01:15.637 --> 00:01:16.847
I'm Seok Jeong-ho, alright?

00:01:16.972 --> 00:01:18.891
You're kidding me.

00:01:19.558 --> 00:01:21.351
I put so much effort into this case!

00:01:21.894 --> 00:01:23.604
Why would you ruin it like this?

00:01:23.687 --> 00:01:26.064
Can't believe you raided this office
without a clue!

00:01:26.356 --> 00:01:27.649
Damn it.

00:01:28.066 --> 00:01:29.651
I was tipped off, okay?

00:01:30.402 --> 00:01:32.654
What a joke.

00:01:42.789 --> 00:01:43.790
Hello?

00:01:44.041 --> 00:01:46.293
There are cryptocurrency scammers
in Gangnam.

00:01:46.376 --> 00:01:47.878
- What?
- Check the files I sent you

00:01:47.961 --> 00:01:49.922
for further details.

00:01:55.719 --> 00:01:57.012
CRIME CASE REPORT
FOR MIRACLE ASIA'S INVESTMENT SCAM

00:01:57.095 --> 00:01:58.180
ALLEGED CRIMES COMMITTED
PAST CHARGES

00:01:58.263 --> 00:01:59.765
THE MANAGEMENT DISAPPEARED IN 2020,
WITH 500 MILLION DOLLARS OF DAMAGE

00:02:05.270 --> 00:02:07.564
Why did you raid this office?

00:02:07.648 --> 00:02:10.484
They're too smart.
They must've caught on...

00:02:14.321 --> 00:02:15.364
Hold on. (Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org)

00:02:20.244 --> 00:02:21.495
Yes, Mr. Lee.

00:02:21.787 --> 00:02:23.956
Did you invest in Miracle Asia?

00:02:24.706 --> 00:02:25.707
No!

00:02:41.974 --> 00:02:43.433
What?

00:02:43.517 --> 00:02:44.726
This can't be right.

00:02:45.185 --> 00:02:46.520
Where did they all go?

00:02:47.854 --> 00:02:48.981
Oh, no.

00:02:49.564 --> 00:02:50.983
CEO'S OFFICE

00:02:54.111 --> 00:02:55.904
These frauds!

00:02:59.408 --> 00:03:00.534
My money!

00:03:05.872 --> 00:03:06.915
My money!

00:03:08.792 --> 00:03:09.876
Mr. Lee

00:03:10.711 --> 00:03:11.753
are you alright?

00:03:12.129 --> 00:03:13.422
It wasn't much money, right?

00:03:13.505 --> 00:03:14.673
How much did you invest?

00:03:16.550 --> 00:03:18.677
You said you'd tell me!

00:03:18.760 --> 00:03:20.345
And that you'd wait two months!

00:03:20.429 --> 00:03:22.097
When did I say that?

00:03:22.848 --> 00:03:24.349
And I wasn't behind the raid.

00:03:41.700 --> 00:03:42.993
Yes, Mr. Kang.

00:03:43.076 --> 00:03:44.911
I got a call from
the Future Talents Foundation.

00:03:47.205 --> 00:03:48.206
Oh, yes.

00:03:48.832 --> 00:03:50.917
Five years of making donations sounds
pretty good.

00:03:51.335 --> 00:03:52.461
Send them 300 million won.

00:03:52.544 --> 00:03:53.545
Yes, sir.

00:04:02.763 --> 00:04:04.306
- The street angel?
- Yes, the angel.

00:04:04.389 --> 00:04:06.558
- I'm Park Cheol-woo.
- I'm Seok Jeong-ho.

00:04:07.309 --> 00:04:08.894
Nice to meet you. I'm Seok Jeong-ho.

00:04:10.520 --> 00:04:14.316
I'll bring you the best food
to go with those drinks.

00:04:15.108 --> 00:04:16.401
Han-young!

00:04:16.485 --> 00:04:18.028
Three billion won!

00:04:18.111 --> 00:04:19.112
Three billion...

00:04:20.864 --> 00:04:23.450
You're paying me for the stage set
and my acting, right?

00:04:23.533 --> 00:04:25.118
- Of course.
- Really?

00:04:25.410 --> 00:04:26.828
You can't lie. You're a judge.

00:04:26.912 --> 00:04:27.913
I wouldn't do that.

00:04:27.996 --> 00:04:29.498
I'll give you all three billion won

00:04:29.581 --> 00:04:31.583
for setting the stage and for your acting.

00:04:31.666 --> 00:04:33.168
And when the time is right

00:04:33.668 --> 00:04:35.712
donate it with a happy heart.

00:04:35.796 --> 00:04:36.797
Hey!

00:04:37.297 --> 00:04:39.216
Nothing's meaner
than taking back a present.

00:04:39.299 --> 00:04:40.967
And nothing is better than sharing.

00:04:41.051 --> 00:04:42.052
No!

00:04:42.135 --> 00:04:43.178
You're the best.

00:04:43.261 --> 00:04:44.805
No, I'm the worst!

00:04:45.263 --> 00:04:47.349
You always let Na-yeong win, but never me.

00:04:47.432 --> 00:04:49.810
You can stop now.
I get it. You two are best friends.

00:04:49.893 --> 00:04:51.895
Won't Sin-jin pass out in stress

00:04:51.978 --> 00:04:53.647
after realizing he's lost three billion?

00:04:53.730 --> 00:04:55.649
It'll be over
before we even break his neck.

00:04:55.732 --> 00:04:58.360
No, I doubt
that he'll be all that affected.

00:04:59.194 --> 00:05:03.115
He knows he can easily earn it back
through blackmail or bribes.

00:05:03.657 --> 00:05:04.658
What?

00:05:04.741 --> 00:05:06.493
So, all that work was meaningless?

00:05:06.576 --> 00:05:07.577
Why meaningless?

00:05:07.661 --> 00:05:09.538
It united us as a team.

00:05:10.580 --> 00:05:12.874
- One team!
- We now know our common enemies

00:05:12.958 --> 00:05:15.961
and how excellent we are
at acting and thinking on our feet.

00:05:17.129 --> 00:05:19.840
Everyone will be so shocked to hear
that the former President is

00:05:20.340 --> 00:05:21.550
on Sin-jin's side.

00:05:21.633 --> 00:05:23.802
- Alright, take your glasses.
- Thanks.

00:05:24.428 --> 00:05:26.179
- What was that? One team?
- Yeah.

00:05:26.263 --> 00:05:27.639
Alright, Jin-a.

00:05:27.722 --> 00:05:28.723
For one team!

00:05:28.807 --> 00:05:30.100
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

00:05:30.517 --> 00:05:31.643
One team!

00:05:31.726 --> 00:05:33.937
We're one! Yes!

00:05:36.148 --> 00:05:38.650
Try this. It's a delicacy.

00:05:38.733 --> 00:05:42.070
Hey, imagine what would've happened
had we not moved offices.

00:05:42.154 --> 00:05:44.489
It was impossible
to get Seong-dae to leave.

00:05:44.865 --> 00:05:45.991
Gosh, we were so close.

00:05:46.366 --> 00:05:48.743
Hearing about that office pisses me off.

00:05:49.161 --> 00:05:50.745
How could you all keep it a secret?

00:05:50.871 --> 00:05:52.205
Well, I went over to help.

00:05:52.289 --> 00:05:53.623
What if I didn't recognize you?

00:05:53.707 --> 00:05:55.041
You recognized me right away.

00:05:55.125 --> 00:05:56.334
All those mean words

00:05:56.418 --> 00:05:58.128
about my driving and life!

00:05:58.545 --> 00:06:00.380
Those words really came from your heart.

00:06:00.464 --> 00:06:03.300
Let's just say I was creative on the spot.
It was all acting.

00:06:03.383 --> 00:06:05.177
Ha, I doubt it.

00:06:05.635 --> 00:06:07.471
Come on, stop picking on me.

00:06:08.472 --> 00:06:10.599
So, what actually happened?

00:06:14.436 --> 00:06:17.189
I tipped the prosecution
about Miracle Asia.

00:06:18.523 --> 00:06:20.150
What? The prosecution?

00:06:20.233 --> 00:06:22.402
We need the prosecution to raid the office

00:06:22.486 --> 00:06:25.405
for the case to be dismissed
without Seong-dae realizing who got him.

00:06:26.490 --> 00:06:27.491
Hey

00:06:30.076 --> 00:06:32.537
how am I supposed to know
the prosecution is coming?

00:06:33.705 --> 00:06:34.706
On that note

00:06:35.999 --> 00:06:37.667
let's set up another office.

00:06:39.169 --> 00:06:42.464
Man, I knew you were smart!

00:06:44.841 --> 00:06:47.385
MIRACLE ASIA HEADQUARTERS ADDRESS

00:06:48.303 --> 00:06:49.804
They moved offices already?

00:06:50.931 --> 00:06:53.642
Classic scammer move.

00:06:54.100 --> 00:06:55.101
Sure.

00:06:55.352 --> 00:06:56.937
Headquarters or not

00:06:57.020 --> 00:06:59.064
as long as they make my money grow.

00:07:00.941 --> 00:07:02.025
You knew it, didn't you?

00:07:02.108 --> 00:07:03.109
No!

00:07:04.486 --> 00:07:06.279
It's my first time hearing about it.

00:07:06.363 --> 00:07:08.698
Wow, your acting is on point!

00:07:11.493 --> 00:07:14.663
What is this?
It's not a restaurant nor a food stand.

00:07:15.705 --> 00:07:17.123
What is this?

00:07:17.207 --> 00:07:18.750
Hello!

00:07:18.833 --> 00:07:20.460
- Hello!
- Hey.

00:07:21.044 --> 00:07:22.128
- Here.
- Hello.

00:07:22.212 --> 00:07:23.213
- Thank you.
- Sit here.

00:07:23.296 --> 00:07:24.589
- Thank you.
- She's...

00:07:25.590 --> 00:07:26.883
How are you?

00:07:27.342 --> 00:07:30.095
Hello, I'm Song Na-yeon.

00:07:31.221 --> 00:07:33.598
Hello, I'm Seok Jeong-ho.

00:07:34.641 --> 00:07:36.017
Hi, I'm Song Na-yeon.

00:07:36.101 --> 00:07:37.477
What's with that voice?

00:07:38.436 --> 00:07:39.729
Have a seat.

00:07:39.813 --> 00:07:40.939
Here.

00:07:41.273 --> 00:07:42.941
I cooked this squid stir-fry.

00:07:43.024 --> 00:07:44.651
- Wow!
- Have a glass.

00:07:45.610 --> 00:07:47.404
Thank you.

00:08:30.530 --> 00:08:32.157
You can beg me all you want

00:08:33.241 --> 00:08:34.659
and I'd still never eat there.

00:08:38.663 --> 00:08:41.041
But why do I want to cry?

00:08:41.124 --> 00:08:42.375
This is so annoying!

00:09:04.939 --> 00:09:09.319
SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT COURT

00:09:10.153 --> 00:09:11.237
SENIOR PRESIDING JUDGE KANG SIN-JIN

00:09:13.615 --> 00:09:14.949
What the hell is this?

00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:17.744
You said you'd sort it out.
You told me to trust you!

00:09:20.622 --> 00:09:22.749
Did I ever say I couldn't sort it out?

00:09:25.752 --> 00:09:27.128
So, what's your plan now?

00:09:27.462 --> 00:09:29.631
Forget becoming the Chief Justice.

00:09:29.714 --> 00:09:32.008
My son is about to make me lose
my Justice title!

00:09:33.843 --> 00:09:36.054
Your son's trial will be over soon

00:09:36.721 --> 00:09:38.556
and you'll become the Chief Justice.

00:09:40.517 --> 00:09:41.518
Are you

00:09:42.477 --> 00:09:43.687
really sure about this?

00:09:45.438 --> 00:09:47.691
The trial was unexpected

00:09:48.066 --> 00:09:50.068
but that won't change anything.

00:09:53.113 --> 00:09:54.364
You're sure about this?

00:09:55.865 --> 00:09:56.866
But

00:09:59.077 --> 00:10:00.620
now that it'll take more effort

00:10:01.579 --> 00:10:04.749
with your son's unexpected case

00:10:07.460 --> 00:10:09.379
you'll need to give me what I want.

00:10:19.597 --> 00:10:21.099
Justice Hwang's son's life is

00:10:21.182 --> 00:10:23.101
right in your hands.

00:10:23.685 --> 00:10:26.396
It's like you won the lottery.

00:10:29.858 --> 00:10:32.152
Justice Hwang's son's life is in my hands

00:10:32.235 --> 00:10:34.237
but nobody's approached me yet.

00:10:35.155 --> 00:10:36.239
As if

00:10:36.656 --> 00:10:38.366
someone is stopping them.

00:10:43.872 --> 00:10:46.249
You cast the bait yourself

00:10:47.375 --> 00:10:49.377
so hunt him yourself, too.

00:10:50.336 --> 00:10:52.380
Tae-seong isn't a bait.
He's being held hostage.

00:11:00.054 --> 00:11:02.140
I'm not conducting a trial.

00:11:02.474 --> 00:11:03.725
It's a hostage situation.

00:11:05.101 --> 00:11:06.644
The record of your illegal funds

00:11:06.728 --> 00:11:08.563
when you worked
for the National Election Commission.

00:11:09.814 --> 00:11:11.357
Bring that to me.

00:11:19.574 --> 00:11:21.326
I don't know what you're talking about.

00:11:28.875 --> 00:11:30.043
Do you really not know?

00:11:30.126 --> 00:11:31.461
No, I don't.

00:11:35.882 --> 00:11:38.134
So, you're choosing to be
a heartless father.

00:11:41.095 --> 00:11:42.138
By the way

00:11:43.223 --> 00:11:46.142
your son will receive
the maximum sentence possible.

00:11:54.359 --> 00:11:56.861
You don't think I can stop a junior judge
with a single call

00:11:56.945 --> 00:11:59.155
with my huge networks?

00:12:00.365 --> 00:12:01.366
Sorry.

00:12:01.449 --> 00:12:04.077
That newbie judge only listens to me.

00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:08.957
Haven't you made enough calls already?

00:12:12.627 --> 00:12:13.628
You must know

00:12:14.379 --> 00:12:17.465
you have zero power over your son's trial

00:12:18.258 --> 00:12:19.759
pretty well by now.

00:12:25.223 --> 00:12:28.518
Anyway, I got your message.

00:12:32.605 --> 00:12:34.399
Regardless of the trial

00:12:35.775 --> 00:12:37.485
I'll make you the Chief Justice.

00:12:39.279 --> 00:12:40.280
The file exposes

00:12:41.447 --> 00:12:43.116
not only multiple assemblymen

00:12:43.199 --> 00:12:46.578
but also the illegal funds
for the former and current Presidents.

00:12:49.122 --> 00:12:50.665
You sure you can handle that?

00:12:55.420 --> 00:12:57.297
I wouldn't have bitten off

00:12:58.131 --> 00:12:59.632
what I couldn't chew.

00:13:14.689 --> 00:13:15.690
Justice Hwang.

00:13:40.298 --> 00:13:41.299
The court hereby orders

00:13:41.716 --> 00:13:43.134
Defendant Lee Bong-seok

00:13:43.384 --> 00:13:46.512
to one year and six months
of imprisonment.

00:13:47.847 --> 00:13:49.390
Hwang Nam-yong.

00:13:56.105 --> 00:13:58.483
I don't care what you give Sin-jin.

00:13:59.901 --> 00:14:02.070
You'll never become the Chief Justice.

00:14:03.488 --> 00:14:05.281
I'll do everything it takes to stop you

00:14:05.740 --> 00:14:07.450
even if you were to sell your soul.

00:14:13.206 --> 00:14:14.624
Why haven't you sent the money

00:14:14.707 --> 00:14:16.000
to the Future Talents Foundation?

00:14:18.878 --> 00:14:21.381
I think we should re-negotiate
on the donation period.

00:14:21.464 --> 00:14:23.841
No, a five-year donation period
isn't a bad deal.

00:14:24.801 --> 00:14:25.802
Right.

00:14:29.555 --> 00:14:30.598
Is something wrong?

00:14:34.310 --> 00:14:36.145
- Mr. Kang.
- Tell me.

00:14:40.149 --> 00:14:41.234
I'm sorry.

00:14:42.026 --> 00:14:43.987
I've been scammed.

00:14:46.280 --> 00:14:47.281
What?

00:14:48.825 --> 00:14:52.704
I invested some money
into an Asian cryptocurrency scam

00:14:53.287 --> 00:14:56.249
and the prosecution ruined my plan
by suddenly raiding them.

00:14:56.791 --> 00:14:58.209
I had no idea.

00:14:58.793 --> 00:15:00.837
You invested your money,
knowing it was a scam?

00:15:01.212 --> 00:15:02.797
Yes. But...

00:15:03.423 --> 00:15:05.508
Prosecutor Park promised a heads-up

00:15:05.591 --> 00:15:06.592
before raiding them

00:15:06.676 --> 00:15:08.636
so I thought it'd be safe.

00:15:09.095 --> 00:15:11.389
But someone unexpected came along...

00:15:11.472 --> 00:15:12.473
That's enough.

00:15:13.641 --> 00:15:14.684
How much did you lose?

00:15:20.982 --> 00:15:23.067
All three billion won.

00:15:25.486 --> 00:15:27.030
You've really lost your mind.

00:15:27.488 --> 00:15:28.823
I can find them.

00:15:29.407 --> 00:15:31.325
Prosecutor Park has been investigating

00:15:31.409 --> 00:15:32.618
so I know he'll find them.

00:15:37.707 --> 00:15:38.708
So?

00:15:39.917 --> 00:15:41.169
What if they do get arrested?

00:15:47.425 --> 00:15:49.010
What will you tell the prosecution?

00:15:58.978 --> 00:16:01.522
How will you explain
where you got the three billion won?

00:16:08.446 --> 00:16:09.906
That I gave it to you?

00:16:28.966 --> 00:16:31.302
I'll do everything to get the money back.

00:16:31.385 --> 00:16:32.595
No!

00:16:43.106 --> 00:16:44.357
Don't bother doing anything.

00:16:56.786 --> 00:16:58.788
Stay low and invisible

00:17:00.123 --> 00:17:01.791
until I call you.

00:17:03.543 --> 00:17:04.836
Just stay alive.

00:17:20.434 --> 00:17:21.561
I'm ready.

00:17:24.021 --> 00:17:25.439
HWANG NAM-YONG

00:17:25.690 --> 00:17:28.234
I'll send the judge
on your son's case tomorrow.

00:17:34.031 --> 00:17:36.659
SENIOR PRESIDING JUDGE KANG SIN-JIN

00:18:15.615 --> 00:18:16.782
You called me?

00:18:20.119 --> 00:18:21.662
Meet up with Nam-yong.

00:18:21.746 --> 00:18:22.747
He has something for you.

00:18:22.830 --> 00:18:23.873
Yes, sir.

00:18:25.708 --> 00:18:27.043
And here.

00:18:30.671 --> 00:18:31.672
What's this?

00:19:15.424 --> 00:19:17.510
So, you're the judge on the case.

00:19:17.593 --> 00:19:19.387
I've seen you at the Central Court.

00:19:20.263 --> 00:19:22.640
Yes, I've only briefly introduced myself.

00:19:22.723 --> 00:19:23.891
Is that right?

00:19:24.517 --> 00:19:26.852
I'm sure you know Tae-seong is my son.

00:19:27.728 --> 00:19:29.397
How do you plan on closing the case?

00:19:30.523 --> 00:19:31.732
What do you mean, sir?

00:19:32.566 --> 00:19:34.485
I guess you haven't heard yet.

00:19:34.986 --> 00:19:36.654
I'll tell you now, then.

00:19:36.737 --> 00:19:39.532
Announce Tae-seong as not guilty.

00:19:40.032 --> 00:19:42.159
Let's say he was misled

00:19:42.243 --> 00:19:44.537
to think his teaching assistantship
and internship

00:19:44.620 --> 00:19:45.997
counted as work experience.

00:19:47.290 --> 00:19:50.501
I'll be forever grateful
once you close the case well.

00:19:51.043 --> 00:19:52.378
And

00:19:55.131 --> 00:19:57.508
make sure to pass this on to Sin-jin.

00:20:01.762 --> 00:20:05.349
If it's about the final verdict,
I've already heard about your history.

00:20:05.766 --> 00:20:08.227
I hear you wrote the verdict yourself
last time.

00:20:08.311 --> 00:20:09.395
If that's what you want

00:20:09.854 --> 00:20:11.981
I'll happily go to that length for you.

00:20:12.064 --> 00:20:14.317
Could you please write one this time, too?

00:20:14.984 --> 00:20:15.985
Sure.

00:20:16.319 --> 00:20:17.987
I just need a few days to write it.

00:20:18.070 --> 00:20:20.614
A person who injures the credit of another
by circulating false facts

00:20:20.698 --> 00:20:22.366
or through fraudulent means

00:20:22.450 --> 00:20:23.909
shall be punished by imprisonment with
labor for less than five years

00:20:23.993 --> 00:20:25.995
or by a fine not exceeding 15 million won.

00:20:27.163 --> 00:20:29.206
What do you think you're doing?

00:20:30.124 --> 00:20:32.251
Just wanted to help you write the verdict.

00:20:32.335 --> 00:20:36.297
Tae-seong lied about his work experience
to apply for the job at JB

